    {
      "id": "670d094b59c8285c35c35a41de23d300dc837042",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 18:59:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nThere are other references of LLOG_SIZE_REPL_CTXT so probably we need to get rid of them as well.\n\n./lustre/include/lustre/lustre_idl.h:3193:\tLLOG_SIZE_REPL_CTXT = 5,\n./lustre/ptlrpc/wiretest.c:3827:\tCLASSERT(LLOG_SIZE_REPL_CTXT == 5);\n./lustre/utils/wirecheck.c:1686:\tCHECK_CVALUE(LLOG_SIZE_REPL_CTXT);\n./lustre/utils/wiretest.c:3839:\tCLASSERT(LLOG_SIZE_REPL_CTXT == 5);",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "7106ac83b8c92d6eee6a9475274abb3dea9dccd1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 19:12:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nMike thought that other unused contexts should be kept so I left them:\n\n \nt:lustre-release# git blame lustre/include/lustre/lustre_idl.h | grep CTXT\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3187) \tLLOG_CONFIG_ORIG_CTXT  =  0,\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3188) \tLLOG_CONFIG_REPL_CTXT = 1,\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3189) \tLLOG_MDS_OST_ORIG_CTXT = 2,\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3190) \tLLOG_MDS_OST_REPL_CTXT = 3, /* kept just to avoid re-assignment */\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3191) \tLLOG_SIZE_ORIG_CTXT = 4,\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3192) \tLLOG_SIZE_REPL_CTXT = 5,\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3193) \tLLOG_TEST_ORIG_CTXT = 8,\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3194) \tLLOG_TEST_REPL_CTXT = 9, /* kept just to avoid re-assignment */\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3195) \tLLOG_CHANGELOG_ORIG_CTXT = 12, /**< changelog generation on mdd */\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3196) \tLLOG_CHANGELOG_REPL_CTXT = 13, /**< changelog access on clients */\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3198) \tLLOG_CHANGELOG_USER_ORIG_CTXT = 14,\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3199) \tLLOG_AGENT_ORIG_CTXT = 15, /**< agent requests generation on cdt */\n8dcfe9e2 (Mikhail Pershin    2014-06-19 23:49:10 +0400 3200) \tLLOG_MAX_CTXTS",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "a4908ee4702966ca2dfa9b6ba2cfe0c48e4f780e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 19:28:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI mean this one: LLOG_SIZE_REPL_CTXT specifically, if you're removing all references to it why bother keeping it?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "14364e15ed3d30b4024d10fe2d56516cd0ffc181",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 19:36:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nBecause Mike specifically restored other unused contexts. See:\n\n \ncommit 8dcfe9e2c0ed6772675e3fb56acf81dbf6ea40d2\nAuthor: Mikhail Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\nDate:   Thu Jun 19 23:49:10 2014 +0400\n\n    LU-5218 llog: keep llog ctxt indices constant\n    \n    The llog context id table cannot be shrinked easily because that\n    will cause index shifting and incompatibility between old client\n    and new server and vice versa.\n    \n    Patch moves llog_ctxt_id table to the lustre_idl.h because this is\n    wire protocol data, these values are added to the wirecheck and\n    checks are added in llog server code for wire data.\n    \n    Signed-off-by: Mikhail Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\n    Change-Id: I003120223504d95164e4392b01c096e3e8b0fef0\n    Reviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/10758\n    Reviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\n    Tested-by: Jenkins\n    Tested-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n    Tested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\n    Reviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "af8cd8bce523f18927e8f0bc6d89553ce3edab09",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 20:07:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI'm a little bit confused here. Usually if a symbol is not used anywhere, we(or you) tend to remove it, and add it back only when we need to use it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "30f5814ea2cc46d489179abb162353d40733a457",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 20:12:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nDid you look at 8dcfe9e2c0ed6772675e3fb56acf81dbf6ea40d2?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "70efedd1c0c5b1a5477e2e71465004016b850359",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 20:23:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nYes, I did. But you can just comment it out and don't change the value of other constants. Is this your concern? Sorry if I missed something here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "481961552b43b1df9227fec45e8f0bc714963bd9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 20:35:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nMike wanted to keep them so I left them. An enum constant has very low runtime and intellectual costs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "e87bf1242d8ca5c805495e1abde4d902646108dd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-10-22 20:49:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nThis is not about runtime cost but make code cleaner as you always do.\n\nTo be honest, I don't think Mike wanted to keep it but he just moved thing around. It's unlikely this enum will be used in near future.\n\nSorry I was too mean to keep talking about this. I'll let you go.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
